rComments: Very entertaining prof! fun and enthusiastic, contemporary and inspiring.  real great introduction to the CCIT program.

A very unhelpful and uncooperative prof, seems full of himself and doesnt care for his students. if you ask him any questions, he will confuse you further..emailing him is useless as you will only get one sentence replies no matter what question you ask. also, assignments are marked hard! difficult to get a 4.0 unless you review past exams
Course is very easy; prof is okay but assignments are little vague..ask a lot of questions and study past midterms! 95% of midterm contained recycled questions

Worst prof I've ever had, I was a first year student extremely excited to take CCT100 but somebody should have warned me about this guy! He rarely shows up to lecture on time/cancels most classes and don't expect an easy grade, you'll find yourself saying "())$$&@8!?,.'," on his tests,assignments and the exam ! Save your money and don't take this
History class but ok once you understand what to look for
worst prof ever. useless lectures. VERY confusing. Took out the interest in this course. Waste of time and money
Attending lecture was useless,study past test will be enough.  Class starts late,finishes early, takes a loooong break.

Very poor teaching style. Rambles off-topic regularly. Takes a long time to get a few simple points across. Always arrives (very) late for class and dismisses students early. Many lectures are cancelled with little or no notice. Even TAs don't care for Prof. Can get A in course by reading textbook, doing past exams & doing online textbook quizzes.
Just get past tests from people who took the course and listen to the lectures, you'll be good to go! His mc are all from questions in past papers

Worst prof ever. Attending to his lecture is totally useless for the mid term or final. Studying past exam maybe helpful. Confusing essay topics and tests questions. Even the TAs have problems with marking the paper.

worst prof ever! Doesn't teach and barely comes to class. What a waste of my money. I can count at least 4 classes in just one semester where he either cancelled (twice), didn't come (had a TA sub in), and late (showed up 1/2 late to a 50 minute lecture).

good lecturer, easy assignments (they are ambiguous and even the TAs had trouble understanding them, but you have a lot of room to write it the way you want to) tests are HARD and pick the most irrelevant information from the texts. for the final he gives you 10 essay topics, one of which will be on, and there will be one other unknown option.

Horrible professor in my opinion. Excruciatingly boring lectures, material in lectures never corroborated with questions in tests/exam. Got a good grade cause I worked my butt off so I'm really glad he doesn't have to lecture me anymore.
His lectures or the textbooks  have nothing to go with the tests. The only people who know their stuff is the TAs.

Loved the course, but not the way he teaches it. Tests are irrelevant to the lectures. Only a few (3 or 4) show up. Need the guidance of the past exams to get 45/50 in the midterm, and nail a 90 in the final.

WORST PROF! I have a feeling he comes on this website & comments positively on himself. TA's are useless esp the program TA-can't speak eng & nobody understood her. Every1 in my class figured out the DW assig themselves. Ext arrogant prof. Useless person and class! Wud rather blast Beyonce in his office than answer emails+concerns from students.
dude doesn't even have a degree in communication/culture (he's a health science guy) but they hire him to teach a foundation course in a communication/culture program... you can sorta tell.
HORRIBLE PROF... HE IS NICE BUT THE TESTS ARE TOO HARD AND THEY DONT MATCH IS LECTURES!!!! WORST PROF EVER!!! WOULD HATE TO TAKE ANOTHER CLASS WITH HIM
A nice guy but doesn't stay on top of marking and updating marks blackboard. His lectures are pretty boring as well.

Very easy going and open minded guy. However, this trait does sort of interfere since its hard to take him seriously (commands little authority). Pay attention to the questions he asks in class (he does this allot) as these are questions you need to be thinking about for assignments/tests/exam.
Useless prof and person.
Completely inefficient in organizing a large class. Pointless lecture slides.

Horrible prof. He should stick to being a doctor. Comes of very arrogant. Although he puts up a different face in the lectures. His assignments are a mess. The TAs don't really care what they mark, the Prof himself is barely present on the campus. Barely answers his emails and thinks way too much of himself.
reallly easy professor....barely went to class and pulled off an 80, his assignments are marked very fairly and the small excercises are a breeze

Prof Moody is a horrible professor. He's a great person but he does not command authority and it makes it hard to take him seriously. The lectures are extremely dull and the assignments and tests are hard and confusing. I only went to the first class and the exam and came out with a B-. No marking structure, dont take this class!
Hardest assignments ever. Not a clear course
Low level of teaching skill that appeals to/satisfies first year students at its best.
Great prof, very approachable. Sometimes the tests/essays can be confusing, but just go to him and ask for help. Definitely recommended.
Don't like Joel at all and wouldn't recommend taking any classes with him, very arrogant guy and  quite stuck up.
Great talker, approachable person but sucks as a prof.
great prof. very approachable and easy on the eyes.

Awesome prof, natural comedian, loves to get the class involved. The tests are brutal!!!! confusing questions. Essays are so random that theres always a lot of research involved - which is good for first year practice...overall a good course and fun prof
BAD

This cat is the coolest teacher I have had.  He is down to earth, cool, calm and looks like one of the members of Boyz II Men.ha Seriously, he is an awesome Prof.  Very motivated and cares a lot about his students. If all Profs were like Joel, everyone's university experiences would be that much more enjoyable. Much respect Joel, we love u big guy!
Excellent prof.  He tries to help us learn material.  I did not like true/false questions on the test, but the essays were ok.

he's a great prof..very helpfull very nice..I didn't like the course tho, it was SUPER easy but his tests oh GOD the craziest multiple choice you can ever have.. they're just very CONFUSING for no reason I mean he picks the least important info to be in the test ... but ya in general he's great teacher and the class was si much fun
good prof.

Can't spell/use proper grammar, makes up words, tries to get us to participate by asking ridiculously obvious questions...horrible at making tests, his multiple choice are awful. Not a hard class, except for the stupid multiple choice, which tend to have debateable answers, and are based often based on totally random bits from the readings.
